<br>
Then you are a gem among EQ players, because unless I ask for money beforehand or get everyone to verbally agree to a split, I rarely make money in a LDoN adventure.  I often lose money in groups.  I ALWAYS Temp the tank and the enchanter (though often the 'chanter declines) for free, but require that anyone else who wants a buff that costs a 'dot to either pay me now or pay me later.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry.  I can't afford any more groups where every other member throws a fit and refuses to enter the dungeon unless I Temp them and then blows off my requests for recompense.  When it costs 50 plat to temp everyone, and the split at the end gets me 50 plat...everyone else made money in that dungeon but me.<br>
<br>
Even polite requests are often met with silence or rude replies that &quot;you're a Cleric, Temping is your job, I'm sure you make money from rezzes anyway&quot; (yeah right, I'm level 48, I have a 75% rez that gets turned down more often than accepted) or even promises that &quot;sure, I'll get you later&quot; that are often forgotten at the end of a dungeon...  &quot;Great group guys, gotta run, wife callin' g'night.&quot;  /camp<br>
<br>
*shrug*  I always explain my position upfront.  MOST people understand it and either hand over some money without a complaint, or the ML promises to give me a cut after the selling.<br>
<br>
If your Cleric was rude about it, well, that's definitely a problem, but it might be because her bank account's been hurting lately from spending that kind of cash on buffing the group and getting sneered at when asking for a little financial aid in return.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, refusing to Pacify unless there was a serious mana-shortage issue is rather sad.  But from personal experience, if I don't have KEI, and a group is moving fast, I really can't Pacify and Heal effectively.  I *don't* throw mana around, but in groups that are efficient and melee-heavy, there's a constant need to be Pacifying OR Healing, leaving very little time to med.<br>
<br>
However, considering that you had a backup healer, it sounds like she might have just been a little too conservative with her mana *or* she was using ineffective heals.  *shrugs*  Couldn't say for certain.<br>
